<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-29"><hi rend="italic">January 29,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Knapp, at Bitlis, charged with murder and inciting rebellion. See Dwight
                            for specifications. If practicable, have immediate investigation and
                            report thereon made by Consul Jewitt. If impracticable for Consul Jewitt
                            to immediately act, ask British ambassador to kindly permit British
                            consul, Yan, to investigate and report upon charges.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>